com.vmware.vapi.protocol

Interface RequestProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JsonOAuthProcessor, JsonSessionProcessor, JsonUserPassProcessor, SecurityContextProcessor

    public interface RequestProcessor
    Implementations of this interface might be attached to client ApiProvider implementations as request post-processors or to the server ApiProvider implementations as request pre-processors.

      • SECURITY_PROC_METADATA_KEY

        static final String SECURITY_PROC_METADATA_KEY
        This key is used to transfer the authentication results to the authentication handlers using the metadata parameter. The object corresponding to the key is expected to be a Map with String key and Object value. Content of the map is authentication handler specific.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Method Detail

      • process

        byte[] process(byte[] requestBytes,
               Map<String,Object> metadata,
               RequestProcessor.Request request)
        Processes and possibly modifies the provided request byte array
        Parameters:
        requestBytes - must not be null. If text is passed as it MUST be UTF-8 encoded.
        metadata - provides additional metadata to the processor that will be passed to the rest of the processor chain. Must not be null. The content under the SECURITY_PROC_METADATA_KEY key will be put in the request's ExecutionContext.SecurityContext under the same key i.e. will be accessible by the authentication handlers.
        request - the vapi request structure. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        the result of the processor. Must not be null. If text is returned it MUST be UTF-8 encoded.
